  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are some memorable lines from popular English songs, each under 70 characters:\n\n1. **\"Imagine there's no heaven.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Imagine\" by John Lennon*\n\n2. **\"You may say I'm a dreamer.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Imagine\" by John Lennon*\n\n3. **\"Cause all of me loves all of you.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"All of Me\" by John Legend*\n\n4. **\"And in the end, the love you take.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"The End\" by The Beatles*\n\n5. **\"Is this the real life? Is this just fantasy?\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen*\n\n6. **\"Every little thing is gonna be alright.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Three Little Birds\" by Bob Marley*\n\n7. **\"We don't need no education.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Another Brick in the Wall\" by Pink Floyd*\n\n8. **\"Because I'm happy\u2014clap along if you feel like happiness is the truth.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Happy\" by Pharrell Williams*\n\n9. **\"You're just too good to be true.\"**  \n   *\u2014 \"Can't Take My Eyes Off You\" by Frankie Valli*\n\n10. **\"Don't stop believin', hold on to that feeling.\"**  \n    *\u2014 \"Don't Stop Believin'\" by Journey*\n\nThese lines have resonated with audiences for their lyrical depth, emotional impact, and timeless quality. If you're looking for more, exploring the lyrics of your favorite artists can uncover many more unforgettable lines!",
